- Tue 15 Oct 2019. CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola)
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/f9cdad998b27/situation-pidmiologique-du-15-octobre-2019?e=37a53d5a9e

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 14 Oct 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3224, of which 3110 are confirmed and 114 are probable. In total, there were 2153 deaths (2039 confirmed and 114 probable) and 1036 people cured;
- 411 suspected cases under investigation;
- 4 new confirmed cases, including 1 in North Kivu in Beni; 3 in Ituri in Mandima;
- no community deaths;
- 3 new deaths of confirmed cases, including 2 in North Kivu -- 1 in Beni and 1 in Mabalako; and 1 in Ituri in Komanda;
- 3 new recoveries released from ETCs , including 2 in North Kivu in Katwa and 1 in Ituri in Komanda;
- no health workers are among the newly confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 161 (5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

Summary of epidemiological data at week 41 (7-13 Oct 2019):
Number of new confirmed cases: 15
Number of new confirmed deaths: 8
Community deaths: 4
Confirmed deaths: 4
Number of new recoveries: 27
Number of health zones removed from the list: 3

