- Sun 13 Oct 2019. CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola)
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us3.campaign-archive.com/?u=b34a30571d429859fb249533d&id=5dce1edd5c

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 12 Oct 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3218, of which 3104 confirmed and 114 probable. In total, there were 2150 deaths (2036 confirmed and 114 probable) and 1032 people cured;
- 429 suspected cases under investigation;
- 6 new confirmed cases to ETCs, including;
- 4 in North Kivu, including 2 in Beni and 2 in Kalunguta;
- 2 in Ituri, including 1 in Mandima and 1 in Nyakunde;
- 2 new deaths of confirmed cases, including 1 community death in North Kivu in Kalunguta; 1 new death in the Beni, North Kivu ETC;
- 1 new recovery released from the ETC in Mambasa, Ituri;
- no health workers are among the newly confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 161 (5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

News
New health area infected with Ebola virus in Ituri
--------------------------------------------------
- A new health area has been affected by Ebola virus disease in Ituri. This is the Maroro health area in the Nyakunde health zone;
- indeed, Nyakunde was already at 294 days without notifying a new confirmed case of the EVD and returned to zero following this new infection;
- of all the 6 cases reported this Sun 13 Oct 2019, none of them were listed as contact, nor monitored regularly, nor vaccinated;
- it is also reported that the alerts of all these cases are coming back from the community and their contacts are being listed, the investigations are continuing, the decontamination of the patients' households is being carried out and the ring of vaccination has been opened around all these cases.

Vaccination
-----------
- Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 237 632 people have been vaccinated;
- the only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 20 May 2018.

Monitoring at entry points
--------------------------
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of checked travelers (temperature measurement) at the sanitary control points is 105 518 454;
- to date, a total of 111 entry points (PoE) and sanitary control points (PoCs) have been set up in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri to protect the country's major cities and prevent the spread of the epidemic in neighboring countries.

